	"__INITIAL_DATA__": {"comments":{"id":27179,"count":44,"talk_id":2561},"threadId":27179,"current_talk":"2561","description":"Summer, 2016: amid populist revolts, clashing resentments and fear, writer Anand Giridharadas doesn't give a talk but reads a letter. It's from those who have won in this era of change, to those who have, or feel, lost. It confesses to ignoring pain until it became anger. It chides an idealistic yet remote elite for its behind-closed-doors world-saving and airy, self-serving futurism — for at times worrying more about sending people to Mars than helping them on Earth. And it rejects the exclusionary dogmas to which we cling, calling us instead to \"dare to commit to the dream of each other.\"","event":"TEDSummit","language":"en","name":"Anand Giridharadas: A letter to all who have lost in this era","slug":"anand_giridharadas_a_letter_to_all_who_have_lost_in_this_era","speakers":[{"id":"2432","slug":"anand_giridharadas","is_published":true,"firstname":"Anand","lastname":"Giridharadas","middleinitial":"","title":"","description":"Writer","photo_url":"https://pe.tedcdn.com/images/ted/3fefe059c10a57427611c0264a5e3a4e91f42fdd_254x191.jpg","whatotherssay":"","whotheyare":"Anand Giridharadas writes about people and cultures caught amid the great forces of our time.","whylisten":"<p>Anand Giridharadas is a writer. He is a&nbsp;<a href=\"http://topics.nytimes.com/top/reference/timestopics/people/g/anand_giridharadas/index.html\" target=\"_blank\"><em>New York Times</em> columnist</a>, writing the biweekly&nbsp;&quot;<a href=\"http://www.nytimes.com/2014/02/18/us/a-tangled-fate-of-prosperity-and-struggle.html\" target=\"_blank\">Letter from America</a>.&quot; He is the author, most recently, of <a href=\"http://books.wwnorton.com/books/The-True-American/\" target=\"_blank\"><em>The True American: Murder and Mercy in Texas</em></a>,&nbsp;about a Muslim immigrant&rsquo;s campaign to spare from Death Row the white supremacist who tried to kill him. In 2011 he published&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/India-Calling-Intimate-Portrait-Remaking/dp/1250001722\" target=\"_blank\"><em>India Calling: An Intimate Portrait of a Nation&#39;s Remaking</em></a>,&nbsp;about&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.nytimes.com/2008/11/23/weekinreview/23anand.html?_r=0\" target=\"_blank\">returning to the India his parents left</a>.</p><p>Giridharadas&#39;s datelines include&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.nytimes.com/2012/10/06/world/europe/06iht-currents06.html\" target=\"_blank\">Italy</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.nytimes.com/2008/06/15/business/worldbusiness/15ambani.html?pagewanted=all\" target=\"_blank\">India</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/Chinese-Dreams-Kindle-Single-ebook/dp/B004JN0CMK\" target=\"_blank\">China</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.nytimes.com/2013/11/26/world/middleeast/dubai.html\" target=\"_blank\">Dubai</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.nytimes.com/2011/07/30/world/europe/30iht-currents30.html\" target=\"_blank\">Norway</a>, Japan,&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.nytimes.com/2011/07/17/magazine/what-is-wyclef-jean-trying-to-save-in-haiti.html?pagewanted=all\" target=\"_blank\">Haiti</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.nytimes.com/2011/11/19/world/americas/19iht-currents19.html?ref=anandgiridharadas\" target=\"_blank\">Brazil</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.nytimes.com/2010/05/02/travel/02cartagena.html?pagewanted=all\" target=\"_blank\">Colombia</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.nytimes.com/2011/10/08/world/africa/08iht-currents08.html?ref=anandgiridharadas\" target=\"_blank\">Nigeria</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.nytimes.com/2014/01/21/world/americas/balancing-private-and-public-needs.html\" target=\"_blank\">Uruguay</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.nytimes.com/2010/02/13/world/americas/13iht-currents.html?ref=anandgiridharadas&amp;_r=0\" target=\"_blank\">the United States</a>. He is an on-air contributor for NBC News and appears regularly on &quot;Morning Joe.&quot; He has given talks on the main stage of TED and at Harvard, Stanford, Columbia, Yale, Princeton, the University of Michigan, the Aspen Institute, Summit at Sea,&nbsp;<a href=\"http://vimeo.com/34926223\" target=\"_blank\">the Sydney Opera House</a>, the United Nations, the Asia Society, PopTech and Google. He is a&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.aspeninstitute.org/leadership-programs/henry-crown-fellowship-program/2011-class\" target=\"_blank\">Henry Crown fellow</a> &nbsp;of the Aspen Institute.&nbsp;</p><p>Giridharadas&nbsp;lives in Brooklyn, New York, with his wife,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://twitter.com/priyaparker\" target=\"_blank\">Priya Parker</a>, and their son, Orion.</p>"}],"url":"https://www.ted.com/talks/anand_giridharadas_a_letter_to_all_who_have_lost_in_this_era","viewed_count":989843,"talks":[{"recommendations":null,"more_resources":[],"corrections":[],"has_citations":false,"take_action":[],"curator_approved":true,"description":"Summer, 2016: amid populist revolts, clashing resentments and fear, writer Anand Giridharadas doesn't give a talk but reads a letter. It's from those who have won in this era of change, to those who have, or feel, lost. It confesses to ignoring pain until it became anger. It chides an idealistic yet remote elite for its behind-closed-doors world-saving and airy, self-serving futurism — for at times worrying more about sending people to Mars than helping them on Earth. And it rejects the exclusionary dogmas to which we cling, calling us instead to \"dare to commit to the dream of each other.\"","downloads":{"id":2561,"languages":[{"languageName":"Finnish","endonym":"Suomi","languageCode":"fi","ianaCode":"fi","isRtl":false},{"languageName":"French","endonym":"Français","languageCode":"fr","ianaCode":"fr","isRtl":false},{"languageName":"Italian","endonym":"Italiano","languageCode":"it","ianaCode":"it","isRtl":false},{"languageName":"English","endonym":"English","languageCode":"en","ianaCode":"en","isRtl":false},{"languageName":"Vietnamese","endonym":"Tiếng Việt","languageCode":"vi","ianaCode