world/americas/13iht-currents.html?ref=anandgiridharadas&amp;_r=0\" target=\"_blank\">the United States</a>. He is an on-air contributor for NBC News and appears regularly on &quot;Morning Joe.&quot; He has given talks on the main stage of TED and at Harvard, Stanford, Columbia, Yale, Princeton, the University of Michigan, the Aspen Institute, Summit at Sea,&nbsp;<a href=\"http://vimeo.com/34926223\" target=\"_blank\">the Sydney Opera House</a>, the United Nations, the Asia Society, PopTech and Google. He is a&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.aspeninstitute.org/leadership-programs/henry-crown-fellowship-program/2011-class\" target=\"_blank\">Henry Crown fellow</a> &nbsp;of the Aspen Institute.&nbsp;</p><p>Giridharadas&nbsp;lives in Brooklyn, New York, with his wife,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://twitter.com/priyaparker\" target=\"_blank\">Priya Parker</a>, and their son, Orion.</p>"}],"speaker_name":"Anand Giridharadas","tags":["collaboration","communication","community","democracy","compassion","fear","government","humanity","history","identity","politics","society","social change"],"title":"A letter to all who have lost in this era","video_type":{"id":"1","name":"TED Stage Talk"},"viewed_count":989843}]}
